longBusinessSummary: Camino Minerals Corporation, an exploration stage company, engages in the exploration and development of mineral properties primarily in Peru. The company explores for copper, gold, and silver deposits. It owns 100% interests in the Plata Dorada project, which consists of 6 claims totaling an area of 2,100 hectares located in the Department of Cuzco, Peru; the Maria Cecilia project covering an area of approximately 7,110 hectares located in the Cordillera Negra Mountain; and the Los Chapitos property comprises 12 claims that covers an area of 6,000 hectares located in department of Arequipa, Peru. The company also has an option agreement to acquire 100% interests in the Red Beds project that comprises three mineral concessions covering an area of 2,500 hectares located in the Department of Cuzco, Peru; and the Lost Cabin project located north east of Lakeview, Oregon. Camino Minerals Corporation was incorporated in 2009 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
